<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,458,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="LC" county="Known" location="Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve" municipality="Santa Marta" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">
Least Concern (
<collectionCode box="[679,719,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">LC</collectionCode>
) in 
<collectingRegion box="[770,878,152,178]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
. 
<collectingCounty box="[891,977,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Known</collectingCounty>
from eight recent collections made at small natural forest fragments in four different localities in central 
<collectingRegion box="[928,1032,190,216]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
(not protected), and 
<specimenCount box="[1276,1436,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingMunicipality box="[215,361,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Santa Marta</collectingMunicipality>
, which is somewhat protected because it forms part of the nuclear zones of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEF90C8F9A8114BB44A:953E60178025FFEF954EFF331472B420" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve</location>
. However, all these montane rain forest habitats, especially in the central region, are still under high anthropogenic pressure. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEF90C8F9A8114BB44A:953E60178025FFEF9263FEE417B3B44A" box="[572,699,306,332]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Specimens" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Specimens</location>
examined: 12; TK collections: 8
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
